<h1>@HI{{bakari}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @Vru{{}} <strong>@HI{{bakari}}</strong>
<li> @Vte{{}} <strong>@HI{{bakari}}</strong>
<li> @Vta{{}} <strong>@HI{{bakari}}</strong>
<li> @Ai{{}} <strong>@HI{{bakari}}</strong>
<li> @Ana{{}} <strong>@HI{{bakari}}</strong>
<li> @N{{}} <strong>@HI{{bakari}}</strong>
<li> @N{{}} <em>particle</em> <strong>@HI{{bakari}}</strong>
<li> <em>quantifier</em> <strong>@HI{{bakari}}</strong>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{bakari}}</strong> is a particle which is indicates which carries the idea of only or of "just done", ""just doing" or "about to do".
</p>

<p>
@Vta{{}} <strong>@HI{{bakari}}</strong> indicates that something has just happened or has just been done. It is the
speaker's feeling that determines whether the action is recent or not.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{sakki @KJ{{daytime}}gohanwo @KJ{{eat}}beta <strong>bakari</strong> desu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    I had lunch just a little while ago.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@Vte{{}} <strong>@HI{{bakari}}</strong> indicates that something is being done, with a nuance that nothing else is being done.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{@KJ{{springtime^creek}}ha@KJ{{cry}}te<strong>bakari</strong>ite@KJ{{what}}mo@KJ{{tale}}soutoshinai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    Harue is crying and won't talk about anything.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@Vru{{}} <strong>@HI{{bakari}}</strong> indicates that something is about to be done.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{kono@KT{{repo-to}}haato@KJ{{tie^argument}}wo@KJ{{write}}ku<strong>bakari</strong>da.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    The only thing left to do with this report is to write a conclusion.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
In classical Japanese <strong>@HI{{bakari}}</strong> expressed the speaker's conjecture and this is still seen
in <em>quantifier</em><strong>@HI{{bakari}}</strong>, which means "about".

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{@KJ{{ten^person}}<strong>bakari</strong>no@KJ{{friend^accomplished}}ga@KJ{{hand^transmit}}ttekuremashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    About 10 friends helped me.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>
</p>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
When <strong>@HI{{bakari}}</strong> follows @HI{{ga}} or @HI{{wo}}, these particles drop. When it follows
@HI{{ni}} or @HI{{he}}, these particles may optionally drop. Other particles remain.
</p>

